The following code takes user input using int 0x21 terminated by enter key and stores it in a buffer whose index 1 has the max size of input, index has the length of input entered by user and index 2 to 80 holds the input itself. First of all, size of user  input is read in bl register and then a '$' is appended at the end of the user input. After ths, the message is printed on console using DOS service 9 and then the using input is printed using the same service.
